# VALIDATION.md Address Linking

## Address Heading Format
State diff sections use headings like:
```
### [`0xaddress`](mdc:link-to-definition) (ContractName) - Chain ID: XXX
```

## Linking Rules
**IMPORTANT**: Keep the original addresses in headings - these represent specific contracts involved in the state diff.

### Finding Address Definitions
Search for each address in superchain-registry files:
- [lib/superchain-registry/superchain/configs/mainnet/](mdc:lib/superchain-registry/superchain/configs/mainnet) - Mainnet contract addresses
- [lib/superchain-registry/superchain/configs/sepolia/](mdc:lib/superchain-registry/superchain/configs/sepolia) - Sepolia contract addresses
- [lib/superchain-registry/validation/standard/](mdc:lib/superchain-registry/validation/standard) - Standard contract versions

### Example Process
1. Keep address: `0x0d83dab629f0e0f9d36c0cbc89b69a489f0751bd`
2. Search: `grep -r "0x0d83dab629f0e0f9d36c0cbc89b69a489f0751bd" lib/superchain-registry/`
3. Found in: `lib/superchain-registry/superchain/configs/sepolia/unichain.toml#L58`
4. Update link: `https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/superchain-ops/blob/main/lib/superchain-registry/superchain/configs/sepolia/unichain.toml#L58`

### Link Format
Always use the full GitHub path with line number:
```
https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/superchain-ops/blob/main/[file-path]#L[line-number]
```

## Common Address Locations
- `OptimismPortalProxy`, `SystemConfigProxy`: Usually in network config files
- `ProxyAdmin`, `AddressManager`: Network-specific addresses
- Implementation addresses: Often in standard-versions files
- `OPCM` addresses: In standard-versions files by upgrade version
